<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2016/07/19/this-week-in-spring-july-19th-2016">This Week in Spring - July 19th, 2016</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/fb22593caf24e4bb4c98d467cdd247e6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/jlong">Josh Long</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2016-07-19 13:44:39.208">July 19, 2016</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2560" href="/blog/2016/07/19/this-week-in-spring-july-19th-2016#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Welcome to another installment of <em>This Week in Spring!</em> This week I am in Cincinnati and Columbus, Ohio, and Los Angeles and San Francisco, California talking to customers and doing meetups.</p>
<p>This is my favorite time of year! As we lead to <strong><a href="http://springoneplatform.io">SpringOne Platform</a></strong>, there’s so much good stuff being released that one can hardly keep up! I am <em>really</em> looking forward to this year’s <strong><a href="http://springoneplatform.io">SpringOne Platform</a></strong> show, coming in early August. It’s an amazing time to build applications, and SpringOne Platform is in a unique position to capture the larger discussion: why do we #devops, #cloud, #agile, or #microservice? Join the discussion August 1-4, 2016 in beautiful Las Vegas and let’s find out!</p>
</div>
</section>
